  <summary date="2015-11-03T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Lifespan Respite Care Reauthorization Act of 2015

This bill amends the Public Health Service Act to extend lifespan respite care programs (services for family caregivers of children and adults with special needs) through FY2020.

Each state agency awarded a grant or cooperative agreement for lifespan respite care must collect, maintain, and report to the Department of Health and Human Services data and records to enable monitoring and evaluation of the lifespan programs and activities.</summary>
